java.util.Scanner;  
public class PerfectNumber 
{  
    {  
long n, perfect=0;  
Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);         
System.out.print("Enter the number: ");  
n=sc.nextLong();  
int i=1;    
while(i <= n/2)  
{  
if(n % i == 0)  
{   
 perfect = perfect + i;  
}  
}  
if(perfect==n)  
{    
System.out.println( "perfect number.");  
}  
else    
System.out.println( "not a perfect number.");   
}  
}





Read a number (n)
Find the factors of the given number (n) by using a loop while.

If both are equal, then the given number is a perfect number.
Else, the number is not a perfect number..
